Distributed Application using RPC in Python for String Concatenation
Theory (Exam Writing)
What is RPC?

RPC (Remote Procedure Call) is a communication mechanism in distributed systems where a client can call a function on a remote server as if it were a local function.

In this application:

Client sends two strings to the server.
Server concatenates the strings.
Result is returned to the client.
Architecture Diagram
